Bring a large #pot{} of salted water to a boil. Wash and dry produce.

Mince @parsley{1/4%ounce}. Zest and quarter @lemon{1}. Peel and mince or grate @garlic{3%cloves}. Thinly slice @sun-dried tomatoes{1.5%ounce}.

Heat a large drizzle of @olive oil{1%tablespoon} in a large, preferably #nonstick pan{}, over medium-high heat. Add @panko breadcrumbs{1/4%cup} and cook, stirring, until golden, ~{3-5%minutes}. Stir in half the parsley, 1/4 tsp @italian seasoning{1%tablespoon} (½ tsp for 4 servings), a big pinch of lemon zest, and a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}. (You'll use more Italian Seasoning in Step 4.)

Turn off heat; transfer to a #plate{}. Wipe out pan.

Heat a drizzle of olive oil in same pan over medium-high heat. Add @spinach{5%ounce}; cook, stirring constantly, until wilted, ~{1-3%minutes}.

Add garlic; cook, stirring, until fragrant, ~{30-60%seconds} more. Season with salt and pepper.

To pan with spinach mixture, add sun-dried tomatoes, @coconut milk{1}, @veggie stock concentrate{1}, 1 tsp italian seasoning (2 tsp for 4 servings), and juice from two lemon wedges (four wedges for 4). Stir to combine. (Save any remaining Italian Seasoning for another use.)

Cook, stirring, until slightly thickened, ~{1-2%minutes}; season with salt and pepper.

Once water is boiling, add @spaghetti{6%ounce} to #pot. Cook, stirring occasionally, until al dente, ~{9-11%minutes}. Reserve 1/4 cup pasta cooking water (½ cup for 4 servings), then drain.

Add drained spaghetti to pan with sauce; toss, adding splashes of reserved pasta cooking water as needed, until everything is coated in a creamy sauce.

Divide pasta between #bowls{}; sprinkle with lemony breadcrumbs and remaining parsley. Serve with remaining lemon wedges on the side.